FBIS4-61227 "drsov087_b_94022" FBIS-SOV-94-087 Daily Report 5 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Space Issues Atomic Weapons Museum Shows `Original' Hydrogen Bomb Atomic Weapons Museum Shows `Original' Hydrogen Bomb LD0405211594 LD0405211594 BFN [Editorial Report] Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian at 1920 GMT on 4 May carries a video report by L. Shesterkina on the atomic weapons museum at (Snezhensk), formerly known as Chelyabinsk 70. The museum shows "the most powerful air-delivered hydrogen bomb in the world" which is, Shesterkina stresses, the original weapon, and not a model. Parts of decommissioned ballistic missiles and explosive devices for civilian purposes are also shown.
